```suggestion
/-- The pushforward of presheaves of modules commutes with the forgetful functor
```
This is a nitpick, so feel free to ignore it, but maybe it's better to write forgetful here? I have no idea which one is "correct", but the main reason for suggesting this is that in the rest of mathlib "forgetful functor" seems to be the norm (searching "forgetful functor" in mathlib gives 304 matches, whereas "forget functor" gives 13).

```suggestion
/-- The pushforward of presheaves of modules commutes with the forgetful functor
```
In case you agree with my other comment, this should also be changed
Can you add some API lemmas? Thanks!
Thanks for the suggestion. I have just added a few (dsimp) lemmas.
